(34, '2016-08-15 03:09:07', '2016-08-15 03:09:07', 0, 'Full Stack Developer', '', 29, 'We\'re looking for Full stack developer\r\nWith extensive experience in both server side and client side.\r\nAt least 4 years of relevant experience and knowledge of the following:\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n·  Extensive experience in web client side technologies: Javascript, JQuery, HTML5, CSS, AJAX.\r\n·  Extensive experience in web server side technologies: ASP.NET\r\n·  Experience in SQL\r\n·  Understands computer networks and how they work ("under the hood" of the networks, and not just "using libraries", e.g. HTTP protocol, how web server works, etc).\r\n·  Experience with object oriented design, software architecture and design patterns.\r\n\r\nAdvantages:\r\n·  MVC\r\n·  Telerik Controls\r\n·  Optimization and tuning.\r\n·  Experience in multi-threaded environment\r\n·  Experience with one of the following libraries: AngularJS, ExtJS, Node.js, Bootstrap, Knockout JS, Polymer, Backbone - advantage.\r\n·  Experience with Database (requirement). optimization and tuning (advantage).\r\n·  Understands computer networks and how they work ("under the hood" of the networks, and not just "using libraries", e.g. HTTP protocol, how web server works, etc).\r\n·  Experience with object oriented design, software architecture and design patterns.\r\n·  Experience with multithreaded environment - an advantage', '', 63, 0, 'Full-time', 10, 322, 10, 324, 10, 325, 10, 140, 10, 323, 0, '1', NULL, 'hgilon@covertix.com'),
(39, '2016-08-18 15:19:29', '2016-08-18 15:19:29', 0, 'R&D Team Leader', '', 30, 'We are looking for a hands-on leader who wants to to lead the web dev team of our fast-growing startup. We\'re a relatively small R&D team of experienced engineers. We\'re very product-oriented and make most of our product decisions within the team, in collaboration with our designers. Each of us takes full ownership of our work and projects, seeing it through from conceptualization to deployment. We believe in short development-cycles and deploy several times a day.\r\n\r\nThis is an excellent opportunity to make an immediate impact in our vision and business goals by leading an agile distributed web development team. The team leader must demonstrate high professional skills, coach his team members, and always strive for excellence.\r\n\r\nThe Role\r\nYou will manage the web dev team which works on dapulse\'s web client and server. You\'ll solve challenging problems ranging from complex and performant UIs (using technologies like React, Angular, Backbone and more) to server and DB performance optimization (working with tools like Ruby on Rails, Redis, Elasticsearch, MySQL, PostgreSQL and more).\r\n\r\nWe believe that you do your best work when you get to work on what interests you the most, so we give our engineers the freedom to focus on what they love.\r\n\r\nWhat you\'ll be doing\r\nLead the design and development of high scale and high performance applications with agile methodologies\r\nWork hands-on with cutting edge open-source technologies\r\nDefine improvement goals for the team and lead the team to achieve those goals\r\nRequirements\r\n2+ years of experience in leading a web development team (3+ team members)\r\nHands-on technical leader/mentor to the team\r\nProfessional growth of the team members\r\nExperience with server side languages such as Ruby, Python, PHP, C# or Java\r\nExperience building a web application from scratch\r\nExperience with client-side JavaScript\r\nExperience with modern browser technologies\r\nStrong communication skills, a positive attitude and empathy\r\nSelf awareness and a desire to improve your skills\r\nBonus Points\r\nAcademic background in computer science\r\nExperience with React, Angular, Backbone, CoffeeScript\r\nExperience with Caching, Server-side optimizations\r\nExperience with writing clean and simple APIs\r\nStrong UI and design skills', '', 59, 0, 'Full-time', 10, 168, 10, 154, 10, 162, 10, 324, 0, 0, 0, '1', '', 'dapulse.devleader@applynow.io'),
(40, '2016-08-18 15:34:40', '2016-08-18 15:34:40', 0, 'Full Stack Developer', '', 30, 'About our engineering team\r\nWe\'re a relatively small team of experienced full-stack engineers, with a variety of backgrounds and skills. We\'re very product oriented and make most of our product decisions within the team, in collaboration with our designers. Each of us takes full ownership of their work and projects, seeing it through from conceptualization to deployment. We believe in short development-cycles and deploy several times a day.\r\n\r\nThe Role\r\nWorking on dapulse\'s web client and server, you\'ll be working on challenging problems ranging from complex and performant UIs (using technologies like React, Angular, Backbone and more) to server and DB performance optimization (working with tools like Ruby on Rails, Redis, Elasticsearch, MySQL, PostgreSQL and more). We believe that you\'ll be doing your best work when you get to work on what interests you the most and so we give our engineers the freedom to focus on what they love and are passionate about.\r\n\r\nWhat you\'ll be doing\r\nBrainstorm with your peers, designers and our CTO to conceptualize new features.\r\nLearn about new web technologies and discuss potential solutions to problems.\r\nHelp our skilled support team triage bugs and troubleshoot production issues.\r\nMentor other engineers and deeply review code.\r\nRequirements\r\nExperience with server side languages such as Ruby, Python, PHP, C# or Java\r\nExperience building a web application from scratch\r\nExperience with client-side JavaScript\r\nExperience with modern browser technologies\r\nStrong communication skills, a positive attitude and empathy\r\nSelf awareness and a desire to improve your skills\r\nBonus Points\r\nAcademic background in computer science\r\nExperience with React, Angular, Backbone, CoffeeScript\r\nExperience with Caching, Server-side optimizations\r\nExperience with writing clean and simple APIs\r\nStrong UI and design skills', '', 55, 1, 'Full-time', 10, 162, 10, 154, 10, 322, 10, 148, 0, 0, 0, '1', '', 'dapulse.fullstack@applynow.io'),
(44, '2016-08-18 16:45:00', '2016-08-18 18:40:09', 0, 'UI/UX Designer', '', 30, 'We are looking for a UI/UX Designer with passion for amazing user experiences to join our team.\r\n\r\nWhat you\'ll be doing\r\nWork on a variety of tasks from product UX to marketing materials.\r\nWork closely with our developers to ensure a successful implementation of your work.\r\nMaintain awareness of the latest industry trends and technologies and provide technical advice to other departments.\r\nThe ideal candidate\r\n2+ years of experience in web design, UI/UX and online marketing materials\r\nKnowledge of website structure and functions\r\nA high level of written and spoken English\r\nExperience with HTML/CSS – Advantage\r\nKnowledge in web marketing - Advantage\r\nAnalytical mind – understanding of A/B testing, reading and understanding stats – Advantage\r\nOrganized, able to prioritize and meet deadlines\r\nTeam player', '', 69, 1, 'Full-time', 2, 18, 2, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '1', '', 'dapulse.uxui@applynow.io'),
(45, '2016-08-18 19:14:13', '2016-08-18 19:14:13', 0, 'R&D Full-Stack Developer', '', 25, 'CyberInt is seeking a Full-Stack Developer to join the R&D development team to improve the End-2-End product features and align the R&D team to the company growth to perform and achieve the development optimization targets and goals of cyber processes. The role will emphasize on development lifecycle from product spec to design, development, testing and deployment following the agile methodology with TDD and BDD implementation to allow continuous deployment based on Python and React.JS coding.\r\nCyberInt is a leading Cyber Intelligence and Cyber Security solution provider. Our company is facing the most advanced and complicated challenges in the Cyber security field. We are looking for a candidate with the passion to learn new skills and a strong understanding of cybersecurity fundamentals in order to develop and to support a highly scalable and maintainable codebase of CyberInt projects.\r\nMain Responsibilities\r\nTeam player with Python and JavaScript hands-on experience that can work with other team members to accomplish various jobs, and to thrive in a collaborative and fast-paced R&D and lab/testing environment.\r\nWorking knowledge of cyber processes, agile development, system operations.\r\nAbility to participate in a multi-task environment\r\nFamiliarity with Support methodologies and practices\r\nAbility to work in a “start-up” environment, initiative to ensure “all bases are covered”\r\nA person that takes ownership and covers the end-2-end\r\nExpected Experience and Knowledge\r\nBachelor’s Degree in Computer Engineering / relevant field\r\nKnowledge and experience with Python\r\nStrong knowledge of React.JS or pure JavaScript\r\nKnowledge of JavaScript frameworks (AngularJS, Ember, Backbone.js, Knockout, React)  (minimum 2)\r\nKnowledge of CSS preprocessor (Less, Sass…) (minimum 1)\r\nStrong knowledge in all aspects of developing single-page web applications\r\nAbility to write high-performance, maintainable, reusable code\r\nProficient in a Unix/Linux environment\r\nKnowledge and understanding of End-2-End systems including Git, Jenkins, AWS, DevOps\r\nStrong leadership and ownership\r\nCapability to promote team-working and collaboration among the different functions, together with an attitude to measure performances by KPIs\r\nBackground in real-time & Big Data technologies/paradigms such as Docker, Redis/RabbitMQ, Elastic Search, MongoDB, AWS and more – a plus\r\nBackground in Machine Learning, NLP or related field – a plus', '', 38, 0, 'Full-time', 10, 322, 10, 146, 10, 149, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '1', '', 'jobs@cyberint.com'),
(46, '2016-08-18 19:39:21', '2016-08-18 19:39:21', 0, 'Cyber Intelligence Analyst', '', 25, 'Our Cyber Intelligence Analysts manage Cyberint intelligence Customers including installing and configuring the customers’ environments into the Cybeint Intelligence platform.\r\nAnalysts help customers with ongoing optimization of cyber, fraud intelligence, provide rapid response to cyber intelligence alerts and emerging threats.\r\nThe analyst trains new customers on the product functionality and features, and addresses initial and post-implementation configuration needs.\r\nThe analyst is responsible for continuous improvement of the customer environment, achieved through the development of new indicators, related to the customer’s specific use-cases.\r\nResponsibilities\r\nCollecting, analyzing, and interpreting qualitative and quantitative data from multiple sources for the purposes of documenting results and analyzing findings to provide meaningful intelligence information.\r\nInvestigating relevant intelligence sources, threat actors, attack tools and techniques.\r\nAnalyzing indicators based on factual information and wider contextual information available.\r\nCharacterizing, Building, and monitoring customers environments, within Cyberint’s unique intelligence platform.\r\nIdentify threats and events within Cyberint’s intelligence platform’s client environments through real time analysis of logs and alerts.\r\nRequirements\r\n2 years’ experience of Cybersecurity; deep understanding of the different attack methods tools and techniques.\r\nFamiliarity with past and current online attack vectors and methods, with a specific understanding of account takeover and step-up authentication concepts.\r\n2-5 years’ experience with intelligence analysis processes, including Open Source Intelligence (OSINT) gathering, source verification, data fusion, link analysis, and threat actors.\r\nAbility to leverage manual and research tools to identify and navigate online forums, specialized Web sites, social media, and traditional sources.\r\nAbility to research and characterize security threats to include identification and classification of threat indicators.\r\nCustomer facing/consulting/servicing background.\r\nFinancial/banking industry cybersecurity threat intelligence familiarity (a plus).', '', 8, 0, 'Full-time', 9, 320, 9, 321, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '1', '', ''),
(47, '2016-08-18 19:47:22', '2016-08-18 19:47:22', 0, 'Software Engineer', '', 31, 'Department: Switching\r\n\r\nDescription: We are looking for highly qualified SW Engineer to join a leading team of SW Developers to contribute to Marvell’s cutting edge technological products.\r\n\r\nIf you have a minimum of 3 years experience in C++ & C# and OO skills and you’re not afraid of challenges – you belong with us!\r\n\r\nJoin the team in all aspects of the software development lifecycle – design, development and deployment support.\r\nDevelop new features in C++, C# infrastructure, automation environment and standalone tools.\r\nMaintain existing features and provide development support.\r\nWork with multiple interfaces such as validation engineers, development leaders and managers to ensure high quality products.\r\nQualifications:\r\n\r\nHands-on C++ & C# programming.\r\nProven experience working with Object oriented SW.\r\nGood knowledge in Design Principles and Design Patterns.\r\nExperience in developing and debugging large high-level software applications with profiling tools.\r\nSoftware analysis and design (preferably using UML modeling)\r\n.NET technologies such as WPF, WCF, WF, ASP.NET MVC, ADO.NET & EF, HTML5 + JS\r\nAdvantage\r\n\r\nFamiliarity with networking protocols.\r\nFamiliarity with data base.\r\nObject oriented multi-threaded/parallel processing.\r\nExperience with Agile engineering practices.', '', 41, 0, 'Full-time', 10, 143, 10, 142, 10, 152, 10, 140, 10, 323, 0, '1', '', ''),
